{"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"9ef9a0f0-22a0-467","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are implementing a ferment for the kubecast project. The ferment ID is `019ea6ea-e768-717f-a8f3-63cd6755637b`, phase ID is `phase-1`. You must call `start_ferment_step`, do the work, then call `complete_ferment_step` for each step sequentially (step-1 through step-11).\n\n## Project Context\n\nThis is a Go project at `/Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast`. The cluster advisor analysis system uses Temporal workflows. Key files:\n\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/workflow/analysis_workflow.go` — Temporal workflow orchestrating analysis\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/workflow/activities.go` — workflow activities  \n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/workflow/types.go` — workflow types\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/handler.go` — variant handler (executor side)\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/handler_test.go` — handler tests\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/handler_component_test.go` — component tests\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/production_simulator.go` — simulation runner\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/types/types.go` — executor signal types\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/repository/types.go` — repository types (AnalysisVariantType, etc.)\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/mq/types.go` — MQ message types\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/snapshots/service.go` — snapshot service\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/debug/service.go` — debug service with context metadata loading\n\n## What Needs to Change\n\n### Issue 1: Descriptive Error Messages (step-1)\nIn `executor/handler.go`, the `failVariant` method sets error to the constant `variantFailedUserMessage = \"simulation failed\"`. Change this to include the root cause: `fmt.Sprintf(\"simulation failed: %s\", cause.Error())`. Be careful to sanitize — strip any full file paths but keep the meaningful error message.\n\n### Issue 2: VariantType in Signals (steps 2-3)\nAdd `VariantType string` field with JSON tag `\"variantType,omitempty\"` to:\n- `executor/types/types.go` `AnalysisVariantCompletedSignal` struct\n- `workflow/types.go` `VariantCompletedSignal` struct\n\nThen in `executor/handler.go`, populate it in:\n- `failVariant` method — set `VariantType: string(variant.VariantType)`\n- Success signal at end of `HandleVariant` — set `VariantType: string(variant.VariantType)`\n- `signalFromVariant` helper — set `VariantType: string(variant.VariantType)`\n\n### Issue 3: Baseline Failure → Analysis Failed (steps 4-5)\nIn `workflow/analysis_workflow.go`:\n- Change `EmitBaselineVariant` result capture from `Get(ctx, nil)` to `Get(ctx, &baselineVariantID)` (add `var baselineVariantID uuid.UUID` before)\n- In the signal handler, when `receivedSignal.Error != \"\"`, check if `receivedSignal.AnalysisVariantID == baselineVariantID`. If so, call `failAnalysis` with a descriptive error like `fmt.Errorf(\"baseline simulation failed: %s\", receivedSignal.Error)` and return immediately.\n\nIn `workflow/types.go`:\n- Add `Error string` field to `FinalizeInput`\n\nIn `workflow/activities.go` `FinalizeAnalysis`:\n- When `input.Status == string(repository.AnalysisStatusFailed)` and `input.Error != \"\"`, set `analysis.Error = &input.Error`\n\nIn `workflow/analysis_workflow.go` `failAnalysis`:\n- Pass the cause error message through to `FinalizeInput.Error`: add `Error: cause.Error()` to the FinalizeInput struct\n\n### Issue 4: Snapshot Fallback for full_cluster (steps 6-7)\nThe snapshot fallback should work in `production_simulator.go`'s `loadSourcePlan` method. Currently when `SourcePlanID == nil && SnapshotAnchorTime == nil`, it calls `GetLatestSnapshot`. After getting the snapshot, the `RunVariant` method calls `LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot` which may fail with \"context location metadata missing\".\n\nThe approach:\n1. Add a method `GetRecentSnapshotLocations(ctx, clusterID, maxAge)` to `snapshots.Service` interface and `RemoteService` that returns snapshot location strings ordered newest-first within the time window, using `storageClient.ListObjectNames`.\n2. In `production_simulator.go`, add a method like `loadSourcePlanWithFallback` that:\n   - First tries the latest snapshot\n   - Calls `LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot` to check metadata\n   - If metadata is missing, gets recent snapshots (up to 5 min) and iterates from newest to oldest\n   - For each, checks if `GetRebalancerDebugContextLocationForSnapshot` succeeds\n   - Returns the first snapshot+context pair that works\n   - This restructures `RunVariant` so the metadata check happens inside `loadSourcePlan` for the full_cluster path\n\nActually, a simpler approach: keep `loadSourcePlan` as-is, but in `RunVariant`, when `LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot` fails with the metadata error AND the request has no `SourcePlanID` and no `SnapshotAnchorTime` (full_cluster path), try the fallback. Add the `snapshotService` to `productionSimulator` (it's already there).\n\n### Steps 8-11: Tests\n- Step 8: Add handler unit tests for descriptive errors and VariantType in signals\n- Step 9: Add snapshot fallback tests\n- Step 10: Add workflow test using Temporal's `testsuite.WorkflowTestSuite`\n- Step 11: Run full test suite\n\n## Important Implementation Notes\n\n- The `AnalysisVariantRequest` in `mq/types.go` does NOT carry `TriggerType`. The full_cluster path is identified by `SourcePlanID == nil && SnapshotAnchorTime == nil`.\n- The `VariantCompletedSignal` in workflow/types.go and executor/types/types.go must stay JSON-compatible (same field names/tags).\n- `repository.AnalysisVariantTypeBaseline = \"baseline\"` and `AnalysisVariantTypeMutation = \"mutation\"` are the variant types.\n- The `Analysis` struct already has an `Error *string` field.\n- The `snapshotTimeWindow` constant in `snapshots/service.go` is currently `time.Minute`. The new `GetRecentSnapshotLocations` should use its own 5-minute window.\n- `storageClient.ListObjectNames` returns a channel. See `GetSnapshotClosestTo` for usage pattern.\n- Test patterns: use `fakeSignaler`, `fakeSimulator`, mockery mocks for repo. See existing tests in `handler_test.go`.\n- For the workflow test, use `\"go.temporal.io/sdk/testsuite\"` — `WorkflowTestSuite` with `TestWorkflowEnvironment`.\n- When writing tests, read the existing test files first to match patterns exactly.\n\n## Execution\n\nFor each step:\n1. Call `start_ferment_step` \n2. Read the relevant files, make the changes\n3. Run the verify command\n4. Call `complete_ferment_step` with gates\n\nWork through steps 1-11 sequentially. Read existing code before editing. Match existing code style."},"timestamp":"2026-06-08T11:19:51.981Z","cwd":"/Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast"}
